<db:section xml:id="details">
<db:title>Detailed Description</db:title>
<db:para>The <db:link xlink:href="qml-qtquick-systempalette.xml">SystemPalette</db:link> type provides access to the Qt application palettes. This provides information about the standard colors used for application windows, buttons and other features. These colors are grouped into three <db:emphasis>color groups</db:emphasis>: Active, Inactive, and Disabled. See the <db:link xlink:href="qpalette.xml">QPalette</db:link> documentation for details about color groups and the properties provided by <db:link xlink:href="qml-qtquick-systempalette.xml">SystemPalette</db:link>.</db:para>
<db:para>This can be used to color items in a way that provides a more native look and feel.</db:para>
<db:para>The following example creates a palette from the Active color group and uses this to color the window and text items appropriately:</db:para>
<db:programlisting language="qml">import QtQuick 2.0

Rectangle {
    SystemPalette { id: myPalette; colorGroup: SystemPalette.Active }

    width: 640; height: 480
    color: myPalette.window

    Text {
        anchors.fill: parent
        text: &quot;Hello!&quot;; color: myPalette.windowText
    }
}
</db:programlisting>
